description: The 3-issue miniseries concludes with a bang! Ami's such an innocent tourist that it's no wonder Yumi's worried about their upcoming trip to Mars! Plus, is there anything Kaz can be good at? The girls will help him find out!
name: Conquer Mars!; Strike A Pose; Oh, Venus!

description: For all 15 years of their lives, Ami and Noa have competed against each other for love with the same results: both fall for the same guy, inevitably scaring him away and leaving them boyfriend-less. But the vicious cycle is broken when the girls go to a party and each fall for two different guys! With potential love on the horizon, the sky couldn't be bluer...until Ami discovers that these two dudes are actually duds with ulterior motives. Determined to get revenge on these players, Ami vows to make her guy fall for her while she trys to protect an unsuspecting Noa!
name: Vol. 1

description: Ami is determined to win Tamon's heart while competing against best friend/rival in love Noa. Things get even more complicated when Tamon's ex-girlfriend Mika shows up on the scene to try and reignite their romance. Frustrated by this unexpected hurdle, Ami seeks advice from "Dr. M." Who is this mysterious love doctor?
name: Vol. 2

description: In spite of Mika, Tamon's meddling ex-girlfriend, Ami is completely determined to win Tamon's heart. Kai, Mika's cousin, shows an interest in Ami which complicates her relationship with Tamon. Has Ami have found a new love interest? Will Tamon finally follow his heart or do what everyone else says?
name: Vol. 3

description: Ami takes off on her long-awaited school trip, where she's determined to make the school "legend" of love come true and confess her feelings towards that special someone. But will Mika foil her plan when she introduces her seductively handsome cousin? Meanwhile, just when things are starting to go great between Ami and Tamon, Nao breaks up with Tomohiro! Will our girls ever find true love?
name: Vol. 4

description: When Ami takes out Tamon on his birthday to the amusement park, the brilliant lights and thrilling rides put her in the mood to finally confesses her feeling toward him! As they become a couple, Ami feels that she can't be happier... Later, Ami meets Sana, a new girl at school, who seems to bond quickly with Ami. But as everybody begins to warn about this "couple crasher," is Ami too blinded by new love to listen?
name: Vol. 5

description: Ami and Tamon participate in the "Couple Competition" and win a vacation trip to Hawaii! But hold on--two's company...and the entire family's a crowd! To Ami's disappointment, both of her parents, Noa and her family, Miyamura and his brother, Sana, and Tomohiro all end up coming along for the ride. Once in Waikiki, Ami meets a mysterious Hawaiian named Kain, who invites Ami to find hidden treasures...Will it all lead to an island-hopping romance?
name: Vol. 6

description: Still in Hawaii, Ami is drawn into Kain's "treasure hunt"...until Tamon comes to try to rescue her--it's a wild chase on the high seas! Kain finds his treasure, a memoir of his first love. Later, a super-suave basketball player appears on the scene. Will this new hottie steal Ami's heart?
name: Vol. 7

description: On Christmas Eve, Sana ends up in a hospital with a broken leg. Tamon is blamed for causing an accident and getting Sana hurt. Tamon ends up staying with Sana at the hospital on Christmas Eve. Is Sana trying to steal Tamon from Ami? Will Ami and Tamon be able to keep a loving relationship?
name: Vol. 8

description: The tale of our favorite love-crazy girls comes to end in this bittersweet final volume. Ami and Tamon's relationship is strained almost beyond repair, no thanks to Sana's devious ploys. Devasted, Ami takes her mind off her problems by playing in a heated basketball tournament against Tamon's school--and her love for Tamon depends on her team's victory or defeat! Will this be the end of Ami and Tamon? Or will it be a slam dunk?
name: Vol. 9

description: The saga of wizardry and magic begins! Thrill to the exploits of Nell, Luka, Luel, and Neo...esoteric Buddhism, secret talismans, mistaken identities, and alchemy of the highest order characterize this intricate supernatural gothic fantasy.
name: Vol. 1

description: The young wizard Luel has been abducted by Sage, his jealous former lover! She has devised a sinister plot to force his hand in marriage! Luel's brother, the Dark Wizard Luka, tries to thwart Sage's plan, battling Fuan, a powerful enchanter taking orders from Sage. Can Luel's pure love for Nell release him from such treachery? Speaking of true love, Leila, desperate to win the apprentice Neo's affection, is busted in Madame Batolli's garden trying to steal herbs for a love potion. The treacherous Fuan offers to assist her but only because she wants to unlock Neo's powerful secret. Maybe Master Cromeheart, Luka's old mentor, will have some answers...
name: Vol. 2

description:
In the depths of a dark and mysterious land, a young boy searches for a secret that can lead to salvation...and more.

Sama is so sad that tears have literally stained his cheeks. His father has fallen gravely ill...and doctors only give him a month to live. With nowhere to turn, Sama grabs his teddy bear and crawls under his bed...magically entering a portal to a fantastic realm called Undertown! Sama looks for the Sugar Stone: a "secret something" that might be able to heal his dad. But The Cloud--the wicked leader of the Insect Insurgents--hunts for the Stone, as well...

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: Sickness, Sadness, and the Legend of Undertown
  • Chapter 2: A Long Way From Home
  • Chapter 3: The Pledge Made At the World's Dirtiest Junkyard
  • Chapter 4: Strange Allies in Strange Alleys
  • Chapter 5: The Sugar Stone Emerges
  • Chapter 6: Rescue From the Hallucination Room
  • Chapter 7: The Teddy Bear Bell
  • Chapter 8: Betrayal At the Butterfly Tree
  • Chapter 9: Final Fight At the Sugar Factory
  • Chapter 10: Father Son, and the Secret That Can Not Be Un-Said
name: Vol. 1

description:
Once, there was a legendary kingdom, called Joseon, an ideal country in which peace and prosperity flourished for years. The heroic warrior Hong Gil-Dong created this Utopian land--and then suddenly disappeared without a trace. But time passed, and a band of ruthless warriors invaded the kingdom, leaving it in utter ruins...

Now, Hong Gil-Dong has returned, determined to raise his village from the ashes. But evil forces lurk in the shadows, observing our hero's every move--waiting for the opportunity to strike down Utopia's avenger... The nonstop martial arts action begins right here!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1 - The Merchant's Daughter
  • Chapter 2 - The Hyeongyeong Master
  • Chapter 3 - Bisasa
  • Chapter 4 - The Fall of Yuldo
  • Chapter 5 - The Last Piece of Yuldo
  • Chapter 6 - The Red Dragon Kings
name: Vol. 1

description:
As the men of Jeongnyongwangbu pursue Gil-Dong, our herp's group splits i two, realizing that his inner force has been disabled, Gil-Dong tries to put up a fight -- but without his power, he may have to resort to something that he promised that he would never, ever use...

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 7 - Poisoned!
  • Chapter 8 - Gwibiyeonhwa
  • Chapter 9 - Cheon Gihu, the Dark Stranger
  • Chapter 10 - Bloody Knuckles
  • Chapter 11 - The Fall of Danu
  • Chapter 12 - Revenge!
  • Chapter 13 - Last Ditch Effort
  • Chapter 14 - A New Foe
name: Vol. 2

description: As Gwibiyeonhwa is mercilessly pummeling Gil-Dong into nothing, Danu is the only one strong enough to rescue Gil-Dong. But his attempt at saving our hero will come at a very high price, and the battle with Gwibiyeonhwa is easy compared to what awaits Hong Gil-Dong on his journey...
name: Vol. 3

description: Gil-Dong finally learns the identity of the mysterious fighter and why Gwanghonhyeolma is after Sanghui. What is the true reason, and what will happen if Gwanghonhyeolma finds Sanghui?
name: Vol. 4

description: Upon arriving at Yachado, Gil-Dong learns that Hyeonwol's Cheonyacha tribe has lost the war against the Jiyachas, and that the chief of the Cheonyacha tribe is being held in the dungeon of Jiyacha castle. Gil-Dong decides to rescue him so he can learn more about the fate of Hyeonwol. Can he successfully infiltrate the castle, and if so, is he ready for Gyeokseong, the Jiyacha's leader?
name: Vol. 5
Happy Feet - L'Eterno Ritorno dei Piedi in Amore

description: Special Issue.
name: Bocca di Rosa
Las Adventuras de Liz y Beth (I)

description:
Changing the face of the galaxy as you know it!

It's all out war as the Sith Empire unleashes its forces and its secret weapons on the rest of the galaxy. As Emperor-in-Exile Roan Fel loses ground against the Sith, he plots to use the enemy's own devices against themregardless of the cost in innocent lives.

Meanwhile, Cade Skywalker has a plan to draw out Darth Krayt for a showdown, a Sith spy within Fel's ranks is revealed, and Fel's own spy meets her fate!

The final chapter of Legacy continues!
name: War Part Two

description: Collects BATMAN IN BARCELONA: DRAGON'S KNIGHT), BATMAN: THE SCOTTISH CONNECTION (illustrated by Frank Quitely), and BATMAN: LEGENDS OF THE DARK KNIGHT #52-53.
name: Batman International

description: This volume presents the comic book adaptations of the major motion pictures BATMAN, BATMAN RETURNS, BATMAN FOREVER and BATMAN AND ROBIN. Based upon the original screenplays, these stories depict the Caped Crusader's legendary battles against the Joker, Two-Face, the Riddler, Catwoman, the Penguin, Mr. Freeze, and Poison Ivy. Also featuring the heroism of Batgirl and Robin, these tales include slight variations and extra scenes from the movies.
name: The Movies

description:
Leather bound HC expanded edition of The Greatest Joker Stories Ever Told.

Foreword by Denny O'Neil, introduction by Mike Gold, afterword by Dick Giordano, end notes by Mark Waid. Includes rare reprints from newspaper strips.
name: The Greatest Joker Stories Ever Told: Expanded Edition

volume.name: Stacked Deck: The Greatest Joker Stories Ever Told: Expanded Edition

description: Some of the greatest animated-style adventures of Batman ever told, collected under one cover! Featuring the Eisner Award-winning BATMAN ADVENTURES: MAD LOVE by Dini & Timm, THE BATMAN ADVENTURES ANNUALS #1 and #2, and tales from THE BATMAN ADVENTURES HOLIDAY SPECIAL #1 and ADVENTURES IN THE DC UNIVERSE #3, this is a must-have volume for any Batman fan. Plus, a commentary on the stories by Timm, who also provides a painted cover!
name: Dangerous Dames & Demons

description: DC's exciting line of digest-sized trade paperbacks expands to include the animated adventures of the Dark Knight Detective! This volume collects GOTHAM ADVENTURES #50 and BATMAN ADVENTURES #1-4, showcasing the worst of Batman's foes in the stories "Second Timers," "No Asylum," "Who Am I?," "Free Man," "Fowl Play," "My Boyfriend's Back," "Breathing Room," and "Need to Know."
name: Vol 1: Rogues Gallery

description: The animated adventures of the Dark Knight Detective make up the newest addition to DC's line of digest-sized collections! This volume collects BATMAN ADVENTURES #5-9, featuring the stories "Shot to the Heart," "Liar Liar," Playing With Matches," "Two Minute Warning," "A Bat in the House," "The First Time," "Masquerade," "Face to Face," "Deathtrap A-Go-Go," and "The Couch."
name: Vol 2: Shadows and Masks

A Goth pop star named Tadeusz is driving young people to imitate vampires and kill people. When a young girl named Mina is inducted into Tadeusz's army of darkness, Nathan Never is hired to track her down and bring her back. Will he be able to save her before she loses her soul? Join Nathan Never as he journeys into the shadows and find out.

Mina Harker, back on Earth, began attending the Wampyr Ensemble, a group of fans of a virtual singer, Tadeusz, led by the sinister "Holy One" .

When Mina disappears, Lucy Seward hires Nathan Never to find her friend.

The traces of the group reveal that the boys are following the virtual tour of the singer. But the "Holy One" wants most: Find the real Tadeusz!

Knowledge is power. And libraries are the key to that power. But what if someone were keeping that power hidden, hoping that one day they would control all information? In Nathan Never's world someone is doing just that and it's up to Nathan to find the hidden library and make its valuable knowledge available to the masses once more. Join Nathan Never on this unique adventure into the Babel Library!

During an attempt to steal an old picture protected by Alfa agents Nathan Never, April Frayn and May Frayn, the girl's father, Donald Frayn, loses his life, and their sister July is injured. Later, Nathan is invited to dinner by a friend, Anthony Russo, a student, but when he comes to Anthony's house, he finds him dead. Through Anthony 's girlfriend, Saki, Nathan discovers that one of the professors of the boy, Marcus Modens, has compromised the computer of the student . In Nathan's future the use of paper (and books) have been abolished, and libraries are one of the very keys to gain absolute power.
name: The Babel Library

description: Wayne goes back to Afghanistan to confront Fariad, an Afghan sniper with the same sonic powers. How far will Wayne go to stop a living bomb? In their epic battle, only one will survive.

Wayne Russell unravels the mystery of how he got back to Chicago, and how a year passed without him noticing. Declared dead in Afghanistan, Wayne's family is under incredible stress and they've had to move back to the inner city. His oldest son is in a gang and they don't like the new stranger who has come to town. They picked the wrong man to mess with.

Wayne Russell tests out his new powers and discovers that someone is watching him. When he tries to track them down, he falls into a trap set by the local gang he encountered last issue. They have a surprise in store for their superpowered nemesis. Meanwhile, halfway around the world, trouble brews in Afghanistan when a man with similar powers emerges.

name: Richie Rich and Jackie Jokers Meet Kool Katz!

description: In the year 2061, three friends grapple with revolutionary change when Sprout Computers releases the most visionary piece of personal technology ever created.

Collecting all 16 issues of Ultimate Marvel Team-Up, plus the star-studded Ultimate Spider-Man Super Special! Teenager Peter Parker may just have started out in the crime-fighting game, but there are plenty of heroes and villains already doing their thing. And it doesn't take long for Spider-Man to encounter these strange new allies and enemies - including Wolverine, the Hulk, Iron Man, the Punisher, Daredevil, the Fantastic Four, the Man-Thing, the X-Men, Doctor Strange, the Black Widow, Shang-Chi and more! Take a wild tour through the ever-exciting Ultimate universe, as Eisner Award-winning writer Brian Michael Bendis teams up with the comic industry's greatest artistic talents! Through the eyes of Peter Parker, Ultimate Marvel Team-Up showcases all the Ultimate heroes. From uncanny mutants to gleaming Avengers to rampaging green brutes, this volume has it all! Collects Ultimate Marvel Team-Up #1-16 and the Ultimate Spider-Man Super Special.
name: Ultimate Marvel Team-Up: Ultimate Collection

description: Spinning out of Supreme Power, hot newcomer Travel Foreman and Joe Straczynski's handpicked writer, Sara "Samm" Barnes, bring to light the secret of Corporal Joe Ledger's dark past, and the plans the crystal has for him! Collects Doctor Spectrum #1-6.
name: Doctor Spectrum: Full Spectrum

description: Kippei has a lot to figure out, like what to make for Yuzuyu's lunch and how to drop her off at kindergarten while still getting to high school on time. Kippei is enjoying his time with Yuzuyu, but not everyone is happy about it. The girls at school miss their quality time with Kippei, and one decides to play dirty to get him back.
name: Vol. 1

description: Kippei is busy trying to become Kokoro's boyfriend and slips back into his irresponsible ways. He oversleeps and doesn't have time to make Yuzuyu's lunch. Even worse, he spends an afternoon with Kokoro, forgetting to pick up Yuzuyu at kindergarten. Yuzuyu feels like she has become a burden to Kippei, so she decides to walk home by herself...and ends up disappearing!
name: Vol. 2
